                            <td>Side effects may peak but body begins adapting</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><strong>Week 4+</strong></td>
                            <td>Most side effects significantly improved or resolved</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><strong>After dose increases</strong></td>
                            <td>Mild return of symptoms for 1-2 weeks, then improvement</td>
                        </tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>

                <h2>Long-Term Success Tips</h2>

                <h3>Build Sustainable Habits</h3>
                <p>Use the medication as a tool to establish healthy patterns:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Regular meal times</li>
                    <li>Balanced, nutritious food choices — browse 500+ GLP-1 friendly recipes in the <a href="index.html#glper-app">GLPer app</a></li>
                    <li>Consistent physical activity</li>
                    <li>Adequate hydration</li>
                    <li>Sufficient sleep</li>
                    <li>Stress management</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Stay in Touch with Your Healthcare Team</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Regular check-ins help optimise your treatment</li>
                    <li>Don't hesitate to discuss side effects—they can adjust your plan</li>
                    <li>Some people benefit from staying at a lower maintenance dose</li>
                    <li>Your pharmacist can provide personalised strategies</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Connect with Others</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Join support groups (online or in-person)</li>
                    <li>Share experiences and tips with others on the same journey</li>
                    <li>Learn from those who've successfully managed side effects</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="callout callout-success">
                    <h4>Remember:</h4>
                    <p>Side effects are typically temporary and manageable. Most people find that by week 3-4, symptoms have significantly improved, and the benefits of appetite reduction and weight loss far outweigh the initial discomfort. You're not alone in this journey—our team at Logan Health is here to support you every step of the way.</p>
                </div>

